cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the deployment and management of Service Function Chains (SFCs) in Software Defined Networking (SDN) and Network Function Virtualization (NFV) architectures, which are primarily related to computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also focuses on security policies and correct policy enforcement, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper presents a formal model for verification, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
